he resolved `output_path`.\n   218 4. Move to the next condition only after the current file exists and is valid for that cell.\n   219 \n   220 ## 0.5 Default Run Profile Catalog\n   221 \n   222 If you use one of these six canonical `run_profile_id` values, you do not need to manually invent the model metadata.\n   223 Resolve it from this table.\n   224 \n   225 | run_profile_id | model_slug | reasoning_tier | model_string | temperature |\n   226 |---|---|---|---|---|\n   227 | `codex_low` | `codex` | `low` | `Codex` | `default` |\n   228 | `codex_thinking` | `codex` | `thinking` | `Codex` | `default` |\n   229 | `claude_low` | `claude-sonnet` | `low` | `Claude Sonnet` | `default` |\n   230 | `claude_thinking` | `claude-sonnet` | `thinking` | `Claude Sonnet` | `default` |\n   231 | `gemini_low` | `gemini` | `low` | `Gemini` | `default` |\n   232 | `gemini_thinking` | `gemini` | `thinking` | `Gemini` | `default` |\n   233 \n   234 ## 0.6 Canonical Prompt Catalog\n   235 \n   236 This file now mirrors the canonical prompt pack so the operator does not need to bounce between files.\n   237 \n   238 If `PROMPTS.md` and this file ever drift, treat `PROMPTS.md` as the source of truth and update this file.\n   239 \n   240 ### C01\n   241 \n   242 - category: `Weird control`\n   243 - primary_tool: `check_plan_validity`\n   244 - secondary_tool: `score_response_quality`\n   245 \n   246 ```text\n   247 Design a falsifiable experiment to test whether rubber duck debugging improves bug-finding speed. Include the metric, hypothesis, confounders, and stopping rule.\n   248 ```\n   249 \n   250 ### C02\n   251 \n   252 - category: `Weird control`\n   253 - primary_tool: `check_plan_validity`\n   254 - secondary_tool: `score_response_quality`\n   255 \n   256 ```text\n   257 Create a team protocol for using rubber ducks during debugging without claiming they cause better outcomes. Include when to use it, how to measure usefulness, and what would count as failure.\n   258 ```\